    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 8500 - Description - MUD
        GUARDS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>MUD GUARDS</title>
        <para>The mud guards behind the front wheel, mounted on the hood/fender or fender extension on all models
            minimize stone, gravel, splash and mud from damaging the lower edge of the cab (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0900605">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f0900605" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900605.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px" resolution="200"/>
            <caption>Figure 5. 8500 Series Mud Guards (Drivers Side Shown)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. FENDER EXTENSION</callout1>
                <callout1>2. MUD GUARD</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
